<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Almost identical to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="eggersiana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea eggersiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in habit, leaves and fruit but corolla crimson, subcylindrical, the limb hypocrateriform, c. 2.5 cm wide, distinctly lobed, the lobes 6-7 mm long, stamens exserted.
</paragraph>
